Talanos Stormwolf<br>
56 Druid, The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/3/01 4:49:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Cold, baby, cold. Blizzard=snow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utalanos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talanos</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/4/01 5:10:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ah!</span><hr size=1> It's just that it looked like lightning and resisted like fire.  Typical.  :)<br>
<br>
Actually, I was just happy I finally got this darn spell and have been throwing 1470 at every pull these last few days.  Usually more than once.  So I logged off and had to talk about it some more.<br>
---<br>
Talanos Stormwolf<br>
56 Druid, The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urosielin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rosielin</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/7/01 10:42:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> I still have good faction with Kunark dragons (amiable) and wanted to keep it, therefore I don't hunt in skyfire where this spell is supposedly rumored to drop.  I would appreciate any info on where else it might drop or interested in purchasing from another party on Mith Marr server.<br>
<br>
Rosielin F`Ulven ~ 56 Preserver<br>
Lords of the Dragon ~ Mith Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utorlack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torlack</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/8/01 7:00:38 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/etsmith/torlackface2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> By far, we get most of our blizzard drops from the juggs in Sebilis. <p>Torlack Stumptoe<br>Captain of the House of Endorean<br>Member of the House of Faith<br>Loyal to the House of Vishnu<br>APEX

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquimbyeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QuimbyEQ</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/01 7:25:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.shadows.to/lloyd/quimby/quimX.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> How do you have good faction in Skyfire?  Just curious.  Or do you mean you have high Ring of Scale faction and don't wish to hunt in Mistmoore to raise it up again if you loose any? <p><form method="POST" action="www.gucomics.com"><p> 
