<option value="char11">Sacred Order of Shadows
</select></form></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugwynetwoodsister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gwynet Woodsister</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/18/01 3:48:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Got one yesterday in Howling Stones, South Wing. <p><center>
Gwynet Woodsister, 
56 Preserver - 
Leorny Blackrose, 51 Disciple<br>
Valiant Elite - Druzzil Ro
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhieran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khieran</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 6:23:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> I hunt in Skyfire a lot (especially wurms of all varieties) and I've killed the named wurms in BW dozens of times helping people get scales for their Wurmslayer quest.  I'm still warmly with Gorenaire.  What mobs in Skyfire hurt your Kunark dragon faction?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 6:54:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Everything but the sperm types will hurt your Kunark dragon faction.<br>
<br>
 <p>-Galipure Stormdancer<BR>Sun Clan of Warriors<BR>Solusek Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 11:31:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> I'm curious what I might have killed to hurt my RoS recently...<br>
<br>
Before I was amiable to Gorenaire. The other day I was running through and conned her at dubious. The only thing I can think of that I might have killed to hurt faction that significantly is Gylton. However, I killed him once a while back in a group, and was still amiable...the only difference this time is that I soloed him. I wonder if it was some kind of bug? I've certainly never been on a Kunark dragon hunt....doh, I just realized I was in on a Faydeder killing....but I didn't think he was on RoS faction? He was scowls even before the fight....does anyone know if Fay gives a RoS hit? I didn't even think to check to be honest. <p><a href="mailto:Cuchulaine@luclin.com">Cuchulaine Kynthelig</a> <BR>
Tunare's Wanderer for 54 Seasons<BR>
<BR>
Luclin
<BR><BR>
"Have you hugged your druid today?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umylene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mylene</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 11:42:48 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/miri311/JEANFACE2.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> I was under the impression that Fay gives a positive faction hit to RoS; something about him being kicked out by the elder dragons.<br>
<br>
-Mylene<br>
Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 12:00:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Were you by chance in wolf form when conning Gorenaire?  She doesn't seem to like wolf form much.  You know I have killed a TON of stuff in skyfire, and Gorenaire was still amiable to me.  I am not sure if this is due to many hours of killing things in MM at lower levels, but I was rather surprised, especially when she stomped a cleric in the guild that I used to hunt with all the time there in Skyfire.  Of course he has sepnt very little time in MM which is why I think that might have something to do with it.  Who knows, maybe the deity difference comes into play as well with mine being Tunare, and his being the one that dwarven clerics follow whichever one that is.<br>
<br>
 <p>-Galipure Stormdancer<BR>Sun Clan of Warriors<BR>Solusek Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 12:02:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> OK, been meaning to ask this anyway.  What good is this spell?  In what situations do you use it?  How do you deal with its taunt effect as well as with its tendency to hit the caster?<br>
<br>
I have made no effort to get Blizzard, as I have never purchased any of the AE cold-based rain spells since the first one.  I just can't see when it would be useful.  I could see it as 1) aggroing all the less-taunted mobs from the pull onto you, 2) breaking a whole hell of a lot of messes and parks, and 3) doing a good bit of damage to you as well as the mobs (by the time you backed off enough to be out of range, you could very well aggro other mobs).  So please enlighten me ... when would this spell be useful/effective, and how do you deal with its side effects? <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>54 Wanderer, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umylene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mylene</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/19/01 6:08:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/miri311/JEANFACE2.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Blizzard is actually nice, under the right conditions.<br>
<br>
It *can* do good damage on a single target. In a group with the critter engaged, step back from the tanks and drop a Blizzard. Three waves of 490 damage puts its damage over Wildfire on a single target for only 10 more mana or so. Of course, has to be one target, and all three waves have to hit for full.<br>
<br>
The AE isn't incredibly large and can be done even with stuff mezzed, provided they are spaced. Also, nowadays pets don't &quot;soak up&quot; a wave of AE rain spells like the did in the past.<br>
<br>
I can't remember how the targeting works for multiple hits (like 2 targets take 2 waves a piece, 3 targets take 1 wave a piece), but this damage if not resisted can be mana efficient. Basically it's situational like other AE spells.<br>
<br>
Disclaimer: I'm not positive on the AE rains no longer counting pets as a target. I know mages asked for this to be removed during the class talks. I have used Blizzard with pets engaged recently and had all 3 waves land, but the pet might of been out of the AE radius.<br>
<br>
-Mylene<br>
Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhieran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khieran</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 3:53:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> >>>Everything but the sperm types will hurt your Kunark dragon faction.<<<<br>
<br>
I've killed hundreds of everything in there and Gorenaire is warmly to me.<br>
<br>
I hunted MM as a younger druid, but not nearly as much as I've killed in Skyfire and Burningwoods.  Strange that I'm still so warm =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udezian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dezian</A></span><br> <b>Registered User</b><br> <font color=#333399>(4/20/01 6:59:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Regarding Blizzard</span><hr size=1> It's faydedar.  I was dubious for over 6 months to gorenaire.  Killed faydedar once and was scowling.  Another druid in my guild was amiably, killed faydedar once, and was down to threatening.  Faydedar seems to be a huge RoS faction hit.<br>
<br>
Shillen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2349.topic"> << Prev Topic </a> &nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2310.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.emailToFriend?topicID=2290.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend">Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.threadControl?topicID=2290.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2290.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2290.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><b>jump to:</b><br><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm16">Velious<option value="thedruidsgrovekunark">Kunark<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgroveclassbalanceissues">Class Balance Issues<option value="thedruidsgrovethetradingpost">The Trading Post<option value="thedruidsgrovedruid